@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Togglo" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The game displays a 7 by 7 tiles board, where each tile has its
own 'backing' tile. Any tile can have one of the following colours:
red, green, blue or yellow. If one coloured tile appears on the
back, lines of its colour will be drawn around the edge of the
facing tile. Clicking on a tile will make it pivot, and the facing
tile will go to the back, and the backing tile will become the
facing tile.

  The goal of the game is to eliminate all the coloured facing
tiles, by creating horizontal and/or vertical alignments of at
least 2 neighbouring tiles that have the same colour. The more
there are neighbouring tiles of the same colour, the more points
you will get.

  Note that the backing tiles are there, either to complicate the
game... or help you, if one ore more of these tiles have the same
colour as a facing tile located next to it. However, as long as
there are neighbouring backing tiles of the same colour, the game
will continue.

  Do not isolate tiles of one colour, that is, a tile as well as
its backing tile that have no neighbouring tile of the same colour.
If that happens, the game will let you find the remaining
neighbouring tiles of the same colour, but after that, the game
will be over.

  When an alignment of tiles of the same colour have been made,
those tiles are then removed from the board and you get points
according to the number of removed tiles; 2 tiles give 1 point...
5 tiles give 64 points.

  When a board has been cleared, then Togglo will generate a new
board and the game will continue...

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or press
the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

@endnode

